SENATE BILL NO. 129
BY SENATOR FOIL AND REPRESENTATIVE CHASSION
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact the Section heading of R.S. 47:463.191, (A), and (C) and to enact
3 R.S. 47:463.243, relative to motor vehicle special prestige license plates; to modify
4 the member of congress special prestige license plate; to establish the "Master
5 Combat Infantryman" special prestige license plate; to provide for creation, issuance,
6 design, fees, distribution, and rule promulgation applicable to the license plate; to
7 provide for an effective date; and to provide for related matters.
8 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
9 Section 1. The Section heading of R.S. 47:463.191, (A), and (C) are hereby amended
10 and reenacted and R.S. 47:463.243 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
11 §463.191. Special prestige license plate; member of congress; designated state
12 officials
13 A. Notwithstanding the provisions of R.S. 47:463(A)(3)(b), the secretary of
14 the Department of Public Safety and Corrections shall establish a special prestige
15 license plate for motor vehicles, restricted to passenger cars, pickup trucks,
16 motorcycles, recreational vehicles, and vans, which may be issued upon application
17 of any Louisiana member of congress, to members of the Louisiana Supreme
18 Court, or upon written request of the clerk of court, for official vehicles used by
19 duly commissioned officers in the course and scope of their official duties.
20 * * *
21 C. The secretary shall promulgate rules and regulations necessary to
22 implement the provisions of this Section, including rules and regulations governing
23 the issuance, transfer, and disposition of the license plates upon the death of the
24 recipient and governing the design of the plate.
25 * * *
26 §463.243. Special prestige license plate; "Master Combat Infantryman"
27 A.(1) The secretary of the Department of Public Safety and Corrections
